The paper deals with the problem of reconstructing a continuous vector from compressed sensing measurements, which is a fundamental problem in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of $L_p$-norm minimization is a common approach in compressed sensing, which falls under numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also utilizes the replica method, which is a statistical physics technique commonly used in compressed sensing (cs.SI). Finally, the problem of compressed sensing has applications in image and signal processing (cs.MM).
